# Mandatory procedures
- **Workflow**: Notes are edited in Obsidian; sync is the user's responsibility (`notes/pollenID/_cli_pid.md` if present).
- **Source of truth**: Notes tagged **SoT: Yes** at the top are treated as verified; all others are `[to be verified]`.

## Do not suggest (hard guardrails)

### Project & documentation hygiene
- **Standalone logs**: No new random log files.
- **Root clutter**: No new root-level clutter except essential configs (`mkdocs.yml`, `.gitignore`, `requirements.txt`, etc.) and focused helpers under **`scripts/`** when the user asks for automation.
- **Redundant plugins**: Check **`mkdocs.yml`** and Material built-ins before proposing new MkDocs plugins.

### Technical & publication
- **Slugs**: Renaming existing `docs/` pages requires an explicit **broken-links / SEO** warning and a small migration plan.
- **Large assets**: Avoid embedding very large images in `docs/` without noting optimization or external hosting.
- **Hardcoded nav**: This project uses explicit `nav` in **`mkdocs.yml`**; do not suggest bulk manual nav edits for every tiny page—prefer batching and link checks.
- **Public/private**: Do not move raw research data from `notes/` to `docs/` unless the user explicitly asks to publish that material.

### Palynology & UI
- **Terminology**: Prefer standard palynological terms.
- **No emojis** never, also not in docs or agent output (see global rules).
- **Mobile**: Avoid layouts that break Material on small screens (huge tables, ultra-wide diagrams).


## Summary of the public MkDocs site structure

docs/
├── index.md
├── Identificatiesleutels/
│   ├── _index.md                     # nav: Keys
│   ├── beug*.md
│   ├── kerkvliet-determinatietabel.md
│   └── pollen-tabel-vanderham.md
├── monoflorale-honing-pollen/
│   ├── _index.md                     # nav: Monofloraal (Overzicht)
│   └── <uniflorale_honing>.md        # nav children (Zonnebloem, ...)
├── pollen/
│   ├── families/
│   │   ├── _index.md                 # nav: Pollen > Families
│   │   └── <family_slug>.md          # Latin family slug (boraginaceae, …)
│   └── species/
│       ├── _index.md                 # nav: Pollen > Species (overview only)
│       └── <pollen_key>.md           # one canonical page per species/type
├── dubbelgangers/
│   ├── _index.md                     # nav: Dubbelgangers (Overzicht)
│   └── <dubbelganger>.md             # nav children (Acer/Amaryllidaceae/Betulaceae/...)
├── naslag/
│   ├── _index.md                     # nav: Naslag
│   ├── synoniemen-en-basioniemen.md
│   ├── pollen-staining-protocols.md
│   └── palynoquest.md                # also nav: Willekeurig
├── assets/                            # shared media (relative paths assets/images/…)
├── stylesheets/
│   └── extra.css                      # in mkdocs.yml
├── javascripts/
│   ├── vdh-pollentabel.js
│   ├── kerkvliet-determinatietabel.js
│   └── palynoquest.js
└── tags.md

Note: Geography/frequency live in `data/pollen.yaml` (`frequency_in_*_honey`, `is_secondary_contributor`), not as separate browse folders. `notes/pollenID/_project_layout_pid.md` may mention stale folders; do not treat those as current layout. Agent docs for scripts live under `.cursor/docs/`, not `docs/naslag/`.
